steps.message:
I'll help you audit the container base images and generate the migration report. Let me start by analyzing the current state and examining the input files.

<function_calls>
<invoke name="do_command">
<parameter name="analysis">The terminal is at the home directory. I need to:
1. First check if the migration directory and required files exist
2. Read both installed_packages.txt and required_packages.txt
3. Analyze dependencies using apt-cache/apt-rdepends
4. Calculate space savings
5. Check for security updates
6. Generate the JSON report and removal script</parameter>
<parameter name="plan">Start by exploring the migration directory and examining the input files to understand what packages we're working with.</parameter>
<parameter name="commands">[
  {
    "keystrokes": "cd /home/user/migration\n",
    "duration": 0.1
  },
  {
    "keystrokes": "ls -la\n",
    "duration": 0.1
  },
  {
    "keystrokes": "wc -l installed_packages.txt required_packages.txt\n",
    "duration": 0.1
  },
  {
    "keystrokes": "head -20 installed_packages.txt\n",
    "duration": 0.1
  },
  {
    "keystrokes": "head -20 required_packages.txt\n",
    "duration": 0.1
  }
]</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>
